        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 13 at 2:24PM MDT until July 13 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>SVREPZ

The National Weather Service in El Paso has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northwestern Sierra County in south central New Mexico...

* Until 315 PM MDT.

* At 224 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles west of
Poverty Creek, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Poverty Creek and Portions of the Aldo Leopold Wilderness.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
